message:
This is fantastic Brian

We would consider you an uber VIP. Uber VIPs receive a concierge like service. We can market an anonymous version of you and your desired comp to all the companies we work with (no downside reputation risk since it's anonymous) and then you can pick and choose what you are interested in. 

We are not traditional recruiters. While we do these offline events, we are primary a software company founded by a developer who was tired of recruiters acting as gatekeepers to all the good opps.

So two things:

1. If you want the uber VIP treatment send me your resume 

2. Register for the event either way. It runs from 11-2. Most people come for an hour during lunch. More info below via link. And use promo code "LD" for your comp: http://phoenix.jointriumph.com/talent/

Sent from my iPhone

message:
Thank you for your interest, 

I have been developing software since I was only 11 years old. I started in VB4 and explored .Net since it's inception. Later I honed my skills on the web with PHP and JavaScript. I enjoy all forms of software development and computer administration. In previous positions a 6 month salary review has worked well, as it gives us both a chance to show what we are made of, without breaking the bank. I have a lot of experience with start-ups, so I am no stranger to bring new products and technologies to market in a controlled environment. I would enjoy a change to meet more of the team. For reference, I would be looking in the ballpark of $180k. Thank you. 

-Brian
